  "market_context": "After a Judas swing off the open, NQ moved higher toward London session highs which were identified as the draw on liquidity. An hourly fair value gap rested below as the next internal liquidity target after external highs were taken.",
  "key_observation": "NQ swept London highs while ES failed to take its corresponding highs, creating an SMT divergence. A 15-minute bearish candle closed back inside, signaling a reversal toward the hourly fair value gap below.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified London highs as the draw on liquidity after the Judas swing off the open.",
    "Zoomed out to the 5-minute chart and confirmed those equal London highs were taken.",
    "Mapped the next target: with externals taken, the hourly fair value gap below became the internal draw.",
    "Dropped to the 15-minute chart to confirm a sweep in the opposite direction of the draw — London highs were swept.",
    "Observed a bearish 15-minute candle close back inside, anticipating that zone to act as resistance pushing price down to the hourly FVG.",
    "Noted ES did not take out its London highs, producing an SMT divergence with NQ at the high.",
    "Dropped to the 1-minute chart, where a second SMT with ES at the high was visible and higher lows formed low resistance liquidity below.",
    "Looked for a 1-minute fair value gap that was traded into and displaced away from; another FVG formed afterward.",
    "Defined the entry at the 1-minute FVG, stop above the swept high, target at the hourly fair value gap."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Combining external-to-internal liquidity logic with SMT divergence across correlated assets (NQ vs ES) and a multi-timeframe sweep + CISD sequence allows precise 1-minute entries targeting HTF fair value gaps with tight, well-defined risk.",
